.TH overlay 3
.SH NAME
\*Loverlay\*O, \*Loverwrite\*O \- Overlays windows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint overlay(\*Vsrcwin\*L, \*Vdstwin\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vsrcwin\*L, \(**\*Vdstwin\*L;\*O

\*Lint overwrite(\*Vsrcwin\*L, \*Vdstwin\*L)
     WINDOW \(**\*Vsrcwin\*L, \(**\*Vdstwin\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "overlay subroutine"
.iX "overwrite subroutine"
The \*Loverlay\*O routine copies all the text from the source window
\*Lsrcwin\*O on top of the destination window \*Ldstwin\*O.
The two windows are not required to be the same size.
The copy starts at (0, 0) on both windows.
The copy is non-destructive, so blanks are not copied.
.PP
The \*Loverwrite\*O routine copies all of \*Lsrcwin\*O
on top of \*Ldestwin\*O.  The copy starts at (0, 0) on both windows.
This is a destructive copy as blanks are copied.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Loverlay\*O and \*Loverwrite\*O functions return OK on
success and ERR on error.
